theorem closure_inter_closure_subset_inter_closures
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    closure ((A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X)) ⊆
      closure (A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `A ∩ closure B` is contained in `A`.
  have hSubA :
      ((A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X)) ⊆ (A : Set X) := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.1
  have hxA : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) := (closure_mono hSubA) hx
  -- `A ∩ closure B` is contained in `closure B`.
  have hSubB :
      ((A : Set X) ∩ closure (B : Set X)) ⊆ closure (B : Set X) := by
    intro y hy
    exact hy.2
  have hxB : x ∈ closure (B : Set X) := (closure_mono hSubB) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB
